### Component 3: `HrtfModule` — Elevation-only comment fix + elevation decoupling

#### [MODIFY] [Modules.cpp](file:///c:/Users/athar/Desktop/Nexus/app/src/main/cpp/modules/Modules.cpp)

Fix the comment: "pinna cascade models pinna reflections that provide **elevation + distance cues**" → "**elevation and front/back discrimination cues**"

Additionally, improve the elevation biquad chain:

**Current elevation model (weak):**
```cpp
pinnaHighL.setHighShelf(13000.0f, elevation * 3.0f, sampleRate);
```
One high shelf above 13 kHz gives minimal elevation impression.

**Improved elevation model (Blauert bands, 1969/1997):**
- Boost at 4 kHz (+3 dB) → front elevation cue
- Notch at 8 kHz (-6 dB) → back/below cue (pinna shadow)  
- Boost at 12 kHz (+2.5 dB) → above-frontal cue
- Use elevation param [0..1] to blend between Blauert-band front (0) and elevated (1) profiles
- This is the basis of KEMAR HRTF measurements — matches AES standard HRTF databases

